    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-16T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-16T02:00:00-05:00" n="1146"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1146">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.62114/9–1644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Political Adviser on the Staff of the
                        Supreme Allied Commander, Mediterranean Theater</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-16T09:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 16, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>411. According to information received at AFHQ<note n="61" xml:id="d1146fn1"
                        >Allied Force Headquarters.</note> from War Office in London an agreement
                    has now been reached with Soviet Government for repatriation of Soviet citizens
                    now or in future held as prisoners of war in Mid East irrespective of whether
                    the individuals desire to return to Russia or not. Statements will not be taken
                    from Soviet nationals in future as to their willingness to return to their
                    native country. Mid East has received instructions from London to implement this
                    agreement and arrange as soon as possible for transfer of these persons to
                    Tehran. Macmillan<note n="62" xml:id="d1146fn2">Harold Macmillan, British
                        Minister Resident at Allied Force Headquarters.</note> is apparently
                    receiving instructions to this effect from the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
